CONFIG DRIVEN UI-swiggy has done it -explaiation =>if some offer is theere in jodhpur n some there is in the delhi so there should be diff ui ?
Yes, that's correct! A config-driven UI allows for dynamic changes in the user interface based on different configurations or conditions. In the case of Swiggy, if there are different offers available in Jodhpur and Delhi, the UI can be designed to display those offers accordingly. This means that users in Jodhpur would see the offers relevant to their location, while users in Delhi would see the offers available in their area. This approach enhances user experience by providing personalized content based on location or other factors.

